               <p>HENRY MOODY. I am a <rs id="t18300916-171-viclabel881" type="occupation">cheesemonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-171-victim1475 t18300916-171-viclabel881"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18300916-171-crimeloc882">Exmouth-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-171-crimeloc882" type="placeName" value="Exmouth-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-171-crimeloc882" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-171-off879 t18300916-171-crimeloc882"></join>. On Saturday, the 24th of July, at half-past eight o'clock in the evening, I saw the prisoner take this bacon, and walk away with it; I pursued, and brought him back with it.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. STURGEON. Q. Was it not late at night? A. No, half-past eight o'clock; I followed him twenty yards - he had not bought it; he was not in the shop at all.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-171-person1476">
                  WILLIAM 
                  WINDER
               <interp inst="t18300916-171-person1476" type="surname" value="WINDER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-171-person1476" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-171-person1476" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I produce the bacon - the prisoner said he bought it at the corner shop; I went there, and they said they had neither seen him nor the bacon.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character.</p>


